        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 3:53PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 353 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Grover, or 39 miles northeast of Greeley, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Keota and Buckingham.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
